{
  "texts": [
    "Channel attention 41, 42 pertains to a mechanism's ability to focus on particular channels of the feature maps selectively.",
    "Typically, this is carried out by computing a set of attention weights for each channel of the feature maps.",
    "These attention weights can then be applied to channels before their transmission through the remainder of the network.",
    "This allows the model to concentrate its prediction on the channels that are most informative.The combination of channel and spatial attention empowers the model to predict using both spatial information (the location of the specified portion within the image) and channel information (the features extracted by the CNN).",
    "This results in more robust and generalizable modelsfor images that have not been seen."
  ]
}